reviews.text: The quality has deteriorated significantly in recent times but the price has still increased. The salad boxes used to be generously filled with reasonable quality ingredients but, with the introduction of the 1kg salad box, the standard one has been reduced in size and the beef chilli is now watery.

Incredibly bad restaurant environment, food was subpar. The restuarant lacks air conditioning system and the inside of the restaurant is incredibly stuffy. Although the restaurant enviornment is below average, this is made up with the extra discounts on food items from other third-party apps such as eatigo. Would not come again unless the air conditioning system is fixed within the restaurant especially during Hong Kong summer!

Worst Cali-mex experience ever. Don’t go this shop. I walked in and ordered takeaway. Had to wait for 25mins. People come after me and food panda order went out before my order with no explanation. The burrito bowls I got was also the worst ever among other shops in HK. The fish was dry, half the size you usually receive from wanchai or pacific place shops. Asked for lettuce instead of cabbage, ended up with no neither. Rice was microwaved dry.

Being from California and accustomed to eating Mexican food frequently....I immediately found my way to Cali-Mex Taqueria. I ordered the chicken tacos (3 to an order), chips and salsa and an ice cold Corona. I added a side of refried beans and guacamole to the taco plate. The shells were crispy and the guacamole fresh. The chicken was cubed but seasoned. My fix was satisfied and would go back again next time I'm in the neighborhood.
Food is not bad, but environment is kinda beat up
